72. What is the difference between fixture scopes?
- Function → runs before every test function  
- Class → runs once per test class  
- Module → runs once per test file  
- Session → runs once for the entire test execution  

Example:
import pytest
@pytest.fixture(scope="module")
def data():
    return "shared"

